Available Tools: get_inbox | get_email | mark_as_read | mark_as_unread | get_unread_count
Call Schema: { "func_call": "string", "folder": "string", "message_id": "string", "limit": number }
Response Schema: { "messages": [{ "id": "string", "from": "string", "subject": "string", "date": "string", "read": boolean }], "total": number }
---
Question: Show me the last 5 emails in my inbox.
Call: { "func_call": "get_inbox", "folder": "INBOX", "message_id": "", "limit": 5 }
Response: { "messages": [{ "id": "msg_9921", "from": "hr@techcorp.com", "subject": "Open Enrollment Period Starts Monday", "date": "2023-10-27T09:15:00Z", "read": false }, { "id": "msg_9920", "from": "newsletter@designweekly.io", "subject": "Top 10 UI Trends for 2024", "date": "2023-10-27T08:30:00Z", "read": true }, { "id": "msg_9919", "from": "support@cloudhost.net", "subject": "Your monthly invoice is ready", "date": "2023-10-26T14:22:00Z", "read": false }, { "id": "msg_9918", "from": "alice.jenkins@partner.org", "subject": "Re: Project Timeline Update", "date": "2023-10-26T11:05:00Z", "read": true }, { "id": "msg_9917", "from": "security@banksecure.com", "subject": "Login attempt from new device", "date": "2023-10-26T09:45:00Z", "read": false }], "total": 5 }

